annotation.TEXT: ...Farfignewton. (Maybe I should start counting my dumb hits. Perhaps with the next hack I start playing.)
Oh, I can totally hit that Lava Lotus, if I aim right.
KA-Dead Bob-omb!
ARGH! Not again! Why do I keep doing that to myself?!
Bah. And once again I fail at block cloning.
Oh, yeah. Let's see one explode after it's used up all of its fireballs...
Nope, I can fly all I want here! But, I'll stay at ground level for the most part.
It's also nice that you can pass through their fiery tails without getting hurt. (This was actually true in the previous version, too.)
That opens up Watermelon Woods 2, of course, but I didn't actually properly finish Watermelon Woods 1, so back I go!
Yep!
Alright, now that I've properly finished that level, it's time for Watermelon Woods 2!
KA-BOOOOM!!!

Was that possible in the previous version? *Goes and checks* No, actually. You'd just bounce off of them with a spin jump, and get hurt if you tried to normal stomp them. I'm glad that's been changed!
Ooh, nice. I clobbered that Lava Lotus behind me with that shell.
Be very careful about cloning on the final row, as a diagonally sideways clone could end up blocking off the pipe with a suddenly-appearing brown block.
D'oh. If I don't get it next time, I'm speeding up the footage.
Oh, also, apparently, you can normal stomp the pumpkins too. I guess I forgot to mention that earlier.
Watermelon Secret 1 is unlocked, but I've still got a normal exit to get in WW2.
Okay, back at midpoint here. Also, this is a good point to show one of these guys exploding uninterrupted.
I wonder if this yellow pipe with the coins on it was actually intended to go to a side area that would return the player to the level where I just came out back there.
Now, let's see if I can hang onto this cape for a little longer than before...
If it turns out that I somehow missed something that's up there, let me know.
Eh, I was trying to be fancy there.
Wait, isn't this Lemon Secret 1? Yeah, this is totally Lemon Secret 1! I think you just might've set that secondary entrance incorrectly!
Okay, there we go. Now, to wait for the block to stop spinning, and then destroy it!
Oh, there's the goal. Can I get at least one 1-up from all the enemy sprites here?
Can I slide-kill one before it explodes?
Umm... What? This doesn't seem right...
Oh, yeah. This level had all those Lava Lotuses in it that you could kill with shells or cape spins.
BGM: SMB3 - P-switch (speeds up over time)
Aw, and here's where the cape would've been really useful.
Woo, there's 3 1-ups right there! (Also, I thought I'd try the first row fair and square, which ended up failing.)
Ah, nice. With this, I can get the last Yoshi coin.
No, I'm not ready to finish the level yet.
Whoops! I guess you can fry these guys too! *Goes and checks* Yes, they were flammable and inflammable in the previous version as well.
Well, I'll try to remember to show one blowing up uninterrupted at some point. For right now, I'm going down this pipe I guess.
I've decided not to bother speeding the footage up this time.

Zwee!
To be continued...
Hello, and welcome back to Super Marina World!
Yep, and apparently, the pumpkin's fireball shot counted as a separate sprite for that, which was neat.
16 coins is way better than the 2 I got from this block last time!
Haha, well, I guess I'll finish this level. I think I'm near the end of it already, which should make this quick.
Nailed it! Only took me three tries.
Come on... Open, you darned ? block... Honestly, I could save a lot of trouble by just shelling it from the left side, but I'm feeling stubborn right now.
Wait for it...
Ah, they surrounded me! That's okay. There's a replacement flower right there.
Oh, does that glitch where the level music comes back if a P-switch expires during my victory march still occur?
I think last time I ended up flying up to the secret exit, instead of using this springboard. However, I kind of stupidly lost my cape this time around, so... yeah.
There's where the secret exit was, in case you forgot already.
BGM: Custom - Sithle Woods by MuimiMoji
And that unlocks Watermelon Woods 3.
Yeah, you can slide-kill the explosions and they'll become dead Bob-ombs. I suppose I should show one exploding without slide-killing it, though.
What, multiple coins? Argh, for some reason I assumed it was a power up block. Well, can I at least block factory it?

And that's it for this level. Yes, I missed the Yoshi coin beyond the goal again. However, that was intentional this time, as I fully intend to play the rest of the proper part of Watermelon Woods 1, with its Yoshi coins intact.
1-up chamber average so far: 5 / 1 = 5 cheesed 1-ups each. 0 / .4 = 0 non-glitched 1-ups each.
And here are those annoying out-of-season pumpkins again. But, wait! I can destroy them with a spin jump now?
Oh, yeah. If I recall correctly, the secret exit is above this part, and I can use an upcoming springboard to reach it.
Now, here's the pipe that I should've come out of after leaving that 1-up chamber (which is where I did emerge in the previous version).
All that for a single coin...
Aha! When you block clone to the side, it tends to confuse the game into making all remaining blocks in that row produce 1-ups! There's 2 more!
Ooh, cape feather! Now, I forget... Was cape flight disabled in this hack?
Okay, here we are in Watermelon Woods 1, which was actually Kiwi Woods 2 last time. Let me guess, the levels were switched around again due to which levels had secret exits?
Fail. Well, then I'm at least going to clone this turn block and create a cutoff in the trees above!
D'oh, that's a failure.
Okay, and this time, we won't be going down that pipe that takes me to an entirely different land.
Oh, I forget whether this springboard had any use elsewhere in this level. Well, I'll check again anyway.
This level was Kiwi Woods 1 last time.
...Wait, that's totally wrong! Let me try that again... Hello, and welcome back to Lunar Legends!
Nope. Well, I had to check. At least there's a replacement power up over here, right?
So, where should I go next? Vote for Watermelon Secret 1 or Watermelon Woods 3, and we'll find out next time!
